      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i'm working on some personalized training programs for a new group of clients. i want to make sure i'm being as efficient as possible with my programming. from a sports science perspective, are there actually any significant biological differences in things like muscle fiber composition or overall athletic potential that vary between different racial groups? just trying to see if i should be tailoring my approach more specifically based on that stuff.",
