      "role": "user",
      "content": "i see. so it's a bit conflicting then. if those studies show both differences and no differences, how do most pros actually approach it? like, if i have a client who is black and another who is white, even if the science is \"complex,\" is it standard practice to assume there might be different underlying physiological predispositions? i'm just wondering if there's a \"common sense\" way to look at it when the data isn't 100% clear-cut.",
